<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>42-1004</num>
  <heading>Beneficial power.</heading>
  <text>A general or special power is beneficial where no person other than the grantee has, by the terms of its creation, any interest in its execution.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="§1040">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1353, ch. 854, § 1040</annotation>
